      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not formally assessed at MRL 2; model form selection (SST k-ω turbulence, power-law hemolysis) is justified by literature precedent.",
      "rationale": "SST k-ω turbulence model and Giersiepen power-law hemolysis model are the community-standard choices for FDA pump CFD as established in the 2011 FDA CFD Round Robin. Formal model form uncertainty quantification is not required at MRL 2 and is scoped out."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not assessed at MRL 2; nominal input values are documented with literature sources.",
      "rationale": "Fluid density (1050 kg/m³), dynamic viscosity (0.0035 Pa·s), and hemolysis model constants are taken from published sources with documented provenance. Sensitivity analysis and input uncertainty propagation are deferred to MRL 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
